IRS990.MissionDescription: ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY PREPARES STUDENTS FOR PROFESSIONAL CAREERS OF SERVICE AND LEADERSHIP, AND PROMOTES THE DISCOVERY AND APPLICATION OF KNOWLEDGE TO IMPROVE THE LIVES OF PEOPLE IN DIVERSE CULTURES AND COMMUNITIES AROUND THE WORLD.
IRS990.Description: ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY IS A NONPROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION ORGANIZED UNDER THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA. THE UNIVERSITY IS AN INDEPENDENT SCHOOL WITH DOMESTIC CAMPUSES LOCATED IN SAN FRANCISCO, FRESNO, LOS ANGELES, IRVINE, SACRAMENTO, AND SAN DIEGO, CALIFORNIA, AND INTERNATIONAL PROGRAMS LOCATED IN MEXICO, JAPAN AND CHINA (AS FURTHER DISCUSSED BELOW). THE PRESIDENT'S OFFICE IS LOCATED IN SAN FRANCISCO. THE UNIVERSITY OFFERS A VARIETY OF ACADEMIC PROGRAMS LEADING TO BACHELORS, MASTERS, AND DOCTORAL DEGREES IN PSYCHOLOGY, BUSINESS, EDUCATION, AND VARIOUS OTHER DISCIPLINES.AS OF JUNE 30, 2010, THE UNIVERSITY OFFERS ITS ACCREDITED PROGRAMS IN MEXICO CITY, MEXICO, THROUGH A SERVICES AGREEMENT WITH COLEGIO DE ADE (FORMERLY RED DE UNIVERSIDADES, A.C., A MEXICAN NOT FOR PROFIT CIVIL ASSOCIATION ("RED")). RED PROVIDES THE UNIVERSITY WITH ON-SITE MANAGEMENT SERVICES AND EXPERTISE WHILE THE UNIVERSITY PROVIDES OVERSIGHT AND AUTHORITY REGARDING ITS ACADEMIC PROGRAMS, FINANCIAL PLANNING, ACCOUNTING, AND EXECUTIVE ADMINISTRATION.THE JAPAN VENTURE WAS FIRST ESTABLISHED IN 2003 WITH THE COLLABORATION OF ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY AND IFF CO., LTD. THIS PROGRAM FOCUSES ON ESTABLISHING AND DELIVERING AN ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY CLINICAL PSYCHOLOGY GRADUATE DEGREE IN JAPAN. THE DEGREE REQUIREMENTS ARE 48 CREDIT HOURS. THE HONG KONG PROGRAM WAS ESTABLISHED IN 2006 WITH THE COLLABORATION OF CALIFORNIA SCHOOL OF PROFESSIONAL PSYCHOLOGY AT ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY AND THE SCHOOL OF CONTINUING AND PROFESSIONAL EDUCATION AT CITY UNIVERSITY OF HONG KONG. THE PROGRAM FOCUSES ON ESTABLISHING A DOCTOR OF PSYCHOLOGY PROGRAM IN CLINICAL PSYCHOLOGY. THE DEGREE REQUIREMENT IS 120 CREDIT UNITS.

Form990ScheduleCPartIV.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION PAYS MEMBERSHIP DUES OF $48,165 TO MEMBER ORGANIZATIONS WHICH MAY ENGAGE IN LOBBYING ACTIVITIES. THEREFORE, A PORTION OF THE DUES MAY BE ATTRIBUTABLE TO LOBBYING ACTIVITIES.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Intended Use of Endowment Funds:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: THE ENDOWMENT FUND IS USED TO FUND SCHOLARSHIPS AND GENERAL OPERATING ACTIVITIES OF THE UNIVERSITY.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The University recognizes and measures tax benefit taken or expected to be taken in an unrelated business activity tax return and discloses any uncertainties in tax positions.

IRS990ScheduleE.PubViaBroadcastMediaExpln: THE UNIVERSITY PUBLISHES ITS NON-DISCRIMINATION POLICY IN A NEWSPAPER OF GENERAL CIRCULATION AND HAS OPERATED IN A BONA FIDE MANNER IN ACCORDANCE THEREWITH.
IRS990ScheduleE.GovtFinancialAidExplanation: ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY IS AN ELIGIBLE INSTITUTION AUTHORIZED BY THE FEDERAL DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION FOR PARTICIPATION IN ITS FEDERAL SCHOOL AID PROGRAMS (TITLE IV, HEA PROGRAMS - OPE ID#0111700) AND ADDITIONALLY RECEIVED FUNDS FROM VARIOUS U.S. AND STATE GOVERNMENT FUNDED PROGRAMS, INCLUDING FUNDS WHICH ARE SUBJECT TO AUDIT BY COGNIZANT GOVERNMENT AGENCIES.THE LOAN FUNDS GROUP CONSISTS OF LOANS TO STUDENTS THROUGH THE FEDERAL PERKINS PROGRAM. THE PRINCIPAL SOURCES OF SUCH FUNDS ARE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT CONTRIBUTIONS, AND REPAYMENT OF PRINCIPAL AND INTEREST, WHICH ARE USED FOR ADDITIONAL LOANS. IF THE PROGRAM IS CANCELLED, FEDERAL CONTRIBUTIONS MAY BE RETURNABLE TO THE GOVERNMENT.

Form990ScheduleFPartIV.Identifier: Method Used to Acccount for Expenditures:
Form990ScheduleFPartIV.Explanation: Schedule F, Part I, Line 3: THE UNIVERSITY USED THE METHOD IT USED FOR ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS TO TRACK EXPENDITURES. The amounts reported are based on the chart of accounts & General ledger for each country, which are tracked separately. The amounts reported are for expenses incurred in country, including normal accruals.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: Procedure for Monitoring Grants in the U.S.:
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: ALL SCHOLARSHIPS AND FELLOWSHIPS MADE BY ALLIANT INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY ARE TO STUDENTS OR FACULTY OF THE UNIVERSITY WHO HAVE COMPLETED AN APPLICATION PROCESS. THE AWARD IS BASED ON A WRITTEN SELECTION CRITERIA. ONCE THE GRANTS ARE DISTRIBUTED, EACH GRANT IS MONITORED ON AN INDIVIDUAL STUDENT ACCOUNT BASIS.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: THE UNIVERSITY PROVIDES OCCASIONAL DISCRETIONARY BONUS PAYMENTS BASED ON PERFORMANCE.

Form990ScheduleLPartIV.Relationship: entity minority owned by Steven Swig, Trustee

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 3
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Alliant International University delegated control over management duties to a management company for operations in Mexico.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 WAS PREPARED IN CONJUNCTION WITH OUTSIDE ACCOUNTANTS FOR SENIOR MANAGEMENT REVIEW. STAFF THEN SUBMITTED THE DRAFT 990 FOR AUDIT COMMITTEE REVIEW AND DISCUSSION AT A COMMITTEE MEETING PRIOR TO FILING. THE FORM 990, AS FILED WITH THE IRS, WAS THEN PROVIDED TO THE FULL GOVERNING BOARD PRIOR TO FILING. THE FINAL FORM IS SIGNED BY THE CFO.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: PURSUANT TO UNIVERSITY POLICY, ON OR BEFORE JUNE 15TH OF EACH YEAR, UNIVERSITY GENERAL COUNSEL CIRCULATES THE UNIVERSITY'S REQUIRED ANNUAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND DISCLOSURE POLICY AND DISCLOSURE FORM TO OFFICERS, TRUSTEES, AND KEY EMPLOYEES FOR REVIEW AND COMPLETION. UNIVERSITY GENERAL COUNSEL REVIEWS ALL DISCLOSURE FORMS AND ADVISES THE AUDIT COMMITTEE ON ANY POTENTIAL OR ACTUAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. THE UNIVERSITY'S POLICY ALSO REQUIRES ALL AFFECTED INDIVIDUALS TO UPDATE AND DISCLOSE CONFLICTS AS THEY ARISE BETWEEN DISCLOSURE CYCLES. UNIVERSITY COUNSEL WOULD, IF A CONFLICT IS DISCLOSED, COUNSEL THE INDIVIDUAL AS TO PROHIBITED TRANSACTIONS. TRUSTEES RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM ANY DISCUSSION AND ACTION RELATED TO POTENTIAL OR ACTUAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES ANNUALLY REVIEWS AND SETS THE COMPENSATION OF THE UNIVERSITY'S PRESIDENT. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE UTILIZES, AT THE COMMENCEMENT OF EACH CONTRACT TERM, COMPENSATION DATA, AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT, AND INDEPENDENT LEGAL COUNSEL TO NEGOTIATE THE PRESIDENT'S CONTRACT. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE ALSO ANNUALLY EVALUATES THE PRESIDENT'S PERFORMANCE. THE PRESIDENT REVIEWS AND APPROVES COMPENSATION FOR OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES. The University's Human Resources department researches and compiles comparative data for the positions using databases from the Chronicle of Higher Education and AICCU in order to benchmark appropriate compensation. The Human Resources department also reviews compensation for all employees to ensure that proposed compensation falls within the University's adopted Employee Classification System.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19: - The University posts the corporate bylaws and charters on its website. Additionally, all governing/organizing documents are available upon request. - The University's conflict of interest policy is disseminated annually to the University Community and is posted on the University's website in a number of locations. Additionally, the policy is distributed upon request. - The University posts the current audited financial statements on the Board of Trustees webpage of the University webiste. Also, the audited financial statements are available upon request. FORM 990, PArt VII: RACHNA KUMAR, MANUEL FIGUEROA, KATHRYN GOLDMAN-SCHUYLER, AND ELAINE BURKE WERE COMPENSATED FOR THEIR ROLES AS FACULTY AT ALLIANT UNIVERSITY AND NOT FOR THEIR ROLES AS TRUSTEES.

20 of the 50 volunteers reported REPRESENT NON-COMPENSATED MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES. STUDENTS AND ALUMNI VOLUNTEER THEIR TIME FOR VARIOUS PURPOSES AT THE UNIVERSITY. THESE VOLUNTEERS, HOWEVER, ARE NOT FORMALLY TRACKED BY THE UNIVERSITY.
